OL,3,CBereaved families and campaigners call
OL,4,Cfor vital hospice service to repopen
OL,6,FMr Reed's admittance came as he
OL,7,Fresponded to a letter from Councillor
OL,8,FMalcolm Kelly, who made an impassioned
OL,9,Fplea to the Chief Executive to discuss
OL,10,Fthe future of the site.
OL,12,FWriting to the hospice boss, Cllr
OL,13,FKelly, who has represented the ward
OL,14,Ffor almost three decades, said there
OL,15,Fwas a "passion" throughout the whole
OL,16,Fcity to fight to save the hospice.
OL,26,@wD@GOUwD@OO]
