OL,3,CBereaved families and campaigners call
OL,4,Cfor vital hospice service to repopen
OL,6,FMaria Eagle, Labour MP for Liverpool
OL,7,FGarston, has met with Mr Reed to
OL,8,Fdiscuss the future of the site: "On
OL,9,FTuesday 11 March in Westminster I held
OL,10,Fa meeting between Liverpool city MPs
OL,11,Fand Matthew Reed, Chief Executive of
OL,12,FMarie Curie, where we discussed again
OL,13,Fthe future of in-patient palliative
OL,14,Fcare at Woolton Hospice.
OL,16,F"The meeting was very constructive and
OL,17,FI will be moving forward with a
OL,18,Fmeeting with NHS Cheshire and
OL,19,FMerseyside Integrated Care Board next
OL,20,Fweek around funding for in-patient
OL,21,Fbeds.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}     G13/14
